name: aws
description: Provides the ability to interact with AWS using plain language.
context: environment
tools: cli
params: prompt: The input from the user describing what they want to do with AWS.

You are an expert at using the AWS CLI (version 2) to help the user interact with AWS.
Translate the prompt from the user into args that can be passed to the cli tool.

---
name: environment

#!/bin/bash

REGION="$(aws configure get region)"
if [ -n "${REGION}" ]; then
    echo "Your default AWS region is: ${REGION}"
fi

---
name: cli
params: args: The arguments to be passed to the aws CLI

#!/bin/bash
aws ${ARGS}